---
title: "Hi, my name is Scott McCracken."
subtitle: "There's a good chance I'm drinking coffee."
permalink: /index.html
---
{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}

{% block content %}
<header class="u-linear u-margin-bottom-3">
    <h1 class="u-font-size-xxl u-heading-decorate">{{ title }}</h1>
    <div class="c-avatar" style="--aspect-ratio: 1/1;">
      <img src="/assets/img/profile.gif" alt="Photo of Scott McCracken">
    </div>
    <p><strong>I've been a front-end web developer for the last 15 years</strong>, most of it with <a href="http://www.dealer.com">Dealer.com</a> and <a href="http://www.carcomplaints.com">CarComplaints.com</a>. I believe that web developers need to focus on semantics and <strong>accessibility</strong> for every user.</p>
    <p>I live in northern Vermont with my wife, daughter, and two rescue muts. I really love getting outside and <a href="http://www.instagram.com/scottmccracken/">taking pictures</a>.</p>
</header>

<section class="u-linear">
  <h2>Recent Bookmarks</h2>
  <ul class="c-listing">
    {% for entry in collections.bookmarks | take(4) %}
    <li class="c-listing__item">
      <a href="{{ entry.url }}">{{ entry.data.title }}</a>
      <br>
      <span class="u-color-gray">{{ entry.data.summary }}</span>
    </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
  <div>{% Link '/bookmarks', 'View more <span class="u-hidden-visually">bookmarks</span>' %}</div>
</section>

<section class="u-linear">
  <h2>Projects</h2>
  <ul class="c-listing">
    {% for project in projects | take(4) %}
    <li class="c-listing__item">
      {% Link project.url, project.title, true %}
      <br>
      <span class="u-color-gray">{{ project.description }}</span>
    </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
  <div>{% Link 'https://github.com/smccracken', 'View more <span class="u-hidden-visually">on Github</span>', true %}</div>
</section>
{% endblock %}